      <p>Because this function squeezes inputs in $(-\infty, \infty)$ into a true probability in $[0, 1]$, I like the name ‚Äúsquishification function‚Äù that <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aircAruvnKk">3Blue1Brown uses</a>, but other people also call it a ‚Äúsquashing‚Äù function.¬†<a href="#fnref:squishification-function" class="reversefootnote" role="doc-backlink">&#8617;</a></p>
